TITLE: Stephanopoulos clashes with Netanyahu on Israel's judicial reforms: Why aren't you taking Biden's 'advice?'
SUMMARY: Benjamin Netanyahu was pressed by ABC's George Stephanopoulos on Thursday over his judicial reform bill, who asked why Netanyahu didn't take President Biden's "advice."

TITLE: Gunman opens fire at Dallas-area medical building, injuring doctor; police shoot, injure suspect
SUMMARY: A man suspected of shooting and injuring a doctor at a medical building in Cedar Hill, located southwest of Dallas, Texas, was confronted and injured by police officers on Tuesday.

TITLE: Explosive detonates near Shiite shrine in Damascus suburb ahead of Ashura holy day, several casualties
SUMMARY: On Thursday, an explosive device planted in a taxi detonated near a Shiite Muslim shrine in the Sayida Zeinab suburb of Damascus, just a day before the holy day of Ashura.

TITLE: Rhode Island police sergeant charged with kicking, striking handcuffed suspect
SUMMARY: Veteran Warwick, Rhode Island police Sgt. Britton Kelly, 55, has been charged with misdemeanor simple assault for allegedly using unwarranted physical force against a handcuffed man.

TITLE: Grand Jury meets on Trump election interference, but no indictment expected Thursday: Court official
SUMMARY: A federal grand jury met in Washington D.C. on Special Counsel Jack Smith's Jan. 6 and election interference investigation, but a court official told Fox News that the panel is not expected to hand up any indictment stemming from the probe Thursday.

TITLE: Watch California woman escape armed carjackers blocking street: 'You've got to be aware'
SUMMARY: A woman in Oakland, California, used quick thinking to flee from two people who tried to carjack her at gunpoint after pulling in front of her car.

TITLE: Florida police release rendering of woman found dismembered in 3 suitcases
SUMMARY: Delray Beach Police revealed Wednesday a rendering of a woman whose body parts were found in three suitcases along the Intracoastal Waterway.

TITLE: Floyd Mayweather Jr's claim he witnessed Tupac Shakur's murder resurfaces amid latest developments in case
SUMMARY: Boxing legend Floyd Mayweather Jr. claims that he was a witness to late rapper Tupac Shakur's shooting in Las Vegas in 1996 while living close to the scene of the crime.

TITLE: Kylian Mbappé trains alone while transfer saga continues
SUMMARY: Soccer superstar Kylian Mbappé is training alone while his PSG teammates are their pre-season tour amid a contract standoff between Mbappé and PSG.

TITLE: Portugal eliminates Vietnam from Women's World Cup with victory in group stage
SUMMARY: Portugal defeated Vietnam 2-0 on Thursday to eliminate Vietnam from the Women's World Cup while Portugal will play the United States in their next match.

TITLE: Canada's Christine Sinclair faces challenge in quest for World Cup history
SUMMARY: Canada's captain Christine Sinclair looks to become the first player to score in six different World Cups, but she had a visible limp after Canada's game against Ireland.

TITLE: White House bats down question on Biden's age after McConnell's freeze
SUMMARY: White House press secretary Karine Jean-Pierre batted down a question about President Biden's age a day after Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell, 81, froze in front of reporters.

TITLE: Mexican authorities capture ‘cloned’ US Border Patrol vehicle in suspected smuggling attempt, 17 detained
SUMMARY: Mexican authorities detained a cloned U.S. Border Patrol vehicle and more than a dozen individuals they suspected were about to be smuggled into the U.S.

TITLE: US congressional committee fails to reach deal on stablecoin bill
SUMMARY: Efforts to establish a federal regulatory framework for stablecoins, a type of cryptocurrency pegged to traditional assets like the U.S. dollar, have hit a roadblock.

TITLE: China's video game player population hits record 668M amid market recovery
SUMMARY: China's video game player population has achieved a new record, reaching 668 million, according to a statement by a government-run game industry association on Thursday.

TITLE: Senate Democrats kill GOP legislation to fly only the American flag from government buildings
SUMMARY: Senate Democrats voted against language on Thursday that would have banned non-U.S. flags from being flown on government property, with some limited exceptions.

TITLE: Giants' Saquon Barkley makes fan's summer after responding to desperate sign at training camp
SUMMARY: One New York Giants fan had a desperate plea on the sign he brought to training camp that needed star running back Saquon Barkley's help to get his ex back.

TITLE: TikTok won't launch cross-border e-commerce services in Indonesia amid concerns
SUMMARY: TikTok has confirmed that it has no intentions of introducing a cross-border e-commerce initiative in Indonesia, amidst concerns expressed by the Indonesian government.

TITLE: Drugmaker Mallinckrodt in talks with hedge funds for potential bankruptcy to avoid opioid settlements
SUMMARY: According to the Wall Street Journal's report on Wednesday, drug manufacturer Mallinckrodt is engaging in discussions with hedge funds about the possibility of filing for bankruptcy.

TITLE: Kuwait executes 5, including perpetrator of 2015 mosque bombing claimed by Islamic State
SUMMARY: Kuwait announced on Thursday that it carried out the execution of five prisoners at the Central Prison, including one who was convicted for his role in the 2015 bombing of a Shiite mosque in Kuwait City.

TITLE: Hunter Biden contradicts dad's claim nobody in family 'made money from China'
SUMMARY: Hunter Biden admitted Wednesday that he received over $600,000 from a Chinese Communist Party-backed company, despite his father's previous denials.

TITLE: El Salvador passes new rules allowing mass trials for accused gang members in crackdown effort
SUMMARY: El Salvador's congress passed a series of new rules aimed at accelerating the legal process for accused gang members in mass trials, as part of President Nayib Bukele's campaign.

TITLE: Nevada district approves sex-ed with phrases ‘boys and people with a penis,’ ‘girls and people with a vulva'
SUMMARY: The school board approved the new sex education curriculum for elementary students, including language like "boys and people with a penis."

TITLE: North Korea opens exhibit celebrating romantic visions of Kim Jong Un for anniversary
SUMMARY: Paintings aim to depict various "victories" for North Korea across its existence with trumped-up images of Kim Jong Un and his father, Kim Jong Il.

TITLE: Dolphins star Jalen Ramsey carted off practice field with apparent knee injury: report
SUMMARY: The Dolphins are holding their collective breaths after trainers attended to Jalen Ramsey during a training camp session. He was then reportedly carted to the locker room.
